main event: A large, cylindrical object with a white flaming trail was sighted climbing straight up over Vero Beach, Florida.
interesting points: The object was reported by multiple aircraft, including Eastern Airlines Flights 635, 635, 638 and National Flight 81, as well as the Nassau Control Tower.
The object was tracked on radar at a position 88 miles from Vero Beach.
The watch supervisor at Miami Center checked with Cape Kennedy, but they reported no knowledge of any activity that could correlate with the sighting.
The report notes that there were no missile launches scheduled that date.
The object's maneuver of climbing straight up suggests it was more likely related to conventional aircraft operations in the vicinity.
sighted object: a large, cylindrical object with a white flaming trail
witnesses: Eastern Airlines Flights 635, 635, 638, National Flight 81, Nassau Control Tower
